1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,798
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:14,014
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,728
[Cita] <i>It's good that you came home.</i>

4
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:22,981
<i>Your father is starting to show illnesses</i>
<i>common among the elderly.</i>

5
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:24,441
[Atoy] <i>How could he not end up like that?</i>

6
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:26,693
<i>I mean, just look at his workplace.</i>

7
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:30,613
[Cita] <i>Who would have thought that</i>
<i>Delfin had been cleaning your room?</i>

8
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:34,034
<i>And yet his wife's grave is left</i>
<i>in such a sorry state.</i>

9
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,994
[Delfin] If your mother were still alive,

10
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:38,121
she wouldn't be pleased
with what you've been doing.

11
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:39,914
If she ever found out everything
you've been up to,

12
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:41,875
she'd be even more upset.

13
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:45,462
It's strange how Mr. Chan hasn't been
coming back here for his fittings.

14
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:48,214
Emerson was the last person he spoke to.

15
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:49,382
[Emerson] <i>Um… What are you doing here?</i>

16
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:51,760
What brings you here?
This isn't the way to your house.

17
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:54,345
I know. Actually, I'm lost.

18
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:56,556
Looks like we've stumbled
onto Traitor's Alley.

19
00:00:56,639 --> 00:01:00,894
[Karla] <i>He even said he should be</i>
<i>the one doing the stitching next time,</i>

20
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:03,021
<i>since you can't handle it anymore.</i>

21
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:04,272
Is it true?

22
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:05,899
[Peping] <i>Did someone move Saint Anthony?</i>

23
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:07,400
[man] <i>I don't think so, Father.</i>

24
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:09,360
We literally just got in.

25
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:13,948
Then why isn't the statue in its place?
Where is it?

26
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:15,742
PREVIOUSLY

27
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,452
What are you going to do?

28
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:18,369
Just leave it to me!

29
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:21,623
[speaks indistinctly]

30
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:24,209
[inquistive music playing]

31
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:26,628
Okay. Thank you.

32
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:27,587
Anytime.

33
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:28,797
Emerson!

34
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,381
- What is it?
- I need to have a word with you.

35
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:33,885
Sir Delfin, today's my day off.

36
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:36,304
Can't we at least have
some work-life balance here?

37
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:38,973
You want me to hit you? Huh? You want?!

38
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:40,725
Have you been taking
my clients behind my back?

39
00:01:41,392 --> 00:01:43,895
Not at all, sir. Why would I even do that?

40
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:46,147
Hey, hey, don't you dare play me
for a fool.

41
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:47,106
You hear me?

42
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:48,191
Just in case you've forgotten,

43
00:01:48,274 --> 00:01:51,486
you had nothing when you first got here.

44
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:53,988
I even lent you money, remember?

45
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:57,617
I also taught you how to sew,
so you could have a skill,

46
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,494
and this is how you pay me back?

47
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:02,247
Sir Delfin, it's just really hard
to ask you for a cash advance.

48
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:04,833
You know very well I've got
a sibling back in the province.

49
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,751
I'm just doing what I can to get by.

50
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,795
Then do it the right way!

51
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:12,924
Not like some snake biting
the very hand that feeds you!

52
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:14,425
You'll never get anywhere
with that attitude.

53
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:15,552
You're bringing misfortune upon yourself!

54
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:18,888
No, you're the one bringing bad luck
on yourself with that kind of attitude.

55
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,515
And don't you dare yell at me like that.

56
00:02:20,598 --> 00:02:23,101
Now I finally understand why
your son doesn't want to see you.

57
00:02:23,184 --> 00:02:24,936
Wow. You've got some nerve.

58
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:27,188
- That was way out of line!
- Enough already.

59
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:29,190
[Emerson] I'm just being honest.

60
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,441
I don't want to be around you anymore.

61
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:33,111
So starting today, I'm done. I quit.

62
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,823
[music continues]

63
00:02:36,906 --> 00:02:38,616
Oh, you have no shame at all.

64
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,201
The nerve to act all upset.

65
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:42,328
Hey, what else did you steal from me?

66
00:02:42,412 --> 00:02:44,247
Give me back my buttons and zippers.

67
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,331
I want those back!

68
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,458
- [mumbling]
- Miss Cita!

69
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:48,877
- [Cita] What?
- Sir Delfin, my goodness,

70
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,837
someone was kidnapped at the church!

71
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,922
Someone was kidnapped! Oh, no!

72
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,549
Listen up, everyone!

73
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,593
Someone's been kidnapped!

74
00:02:56,676 --> 00:03:00,013
[mysterious music playing]

75
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:02,807
What happened?

76
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:04,517
Who was kidnapped?

77
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:06,060
No one was actually kidnapped.

78
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:09,689
Delfin, the statue is missing.

79
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:12,358
Someone stole Saint Anthony of Padua.

80
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:13,443
[Cita] What?

81
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:16,946
Our Patron Saint was kidnapped,
Sir Delfin. My God.

82
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:20,033
But who would do such a thing?

83
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:22,827
And why would they do it
right before the fiesta?

84
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:25,246
Someone wants to sabotage us.

85
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:27,457
Oh, I'm sure whoever did this
is not from here.

86
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,667
It's probably someone from another town.

87
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:31,711
Munggo, did you happen to have
any enemies during the game?

88
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:35,048
But why would
they drag our patron into it?

89
00:03:35,131 --> 00:03:36,591
All over a basketball game?

90
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,969
This is the first time Saint Anthony
has gone missing.

91
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:45,433
- I'm sure whoever stole it is new here.
- [crowd] Could be.

92
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:49,896
Someone who grew up
with no respect for our patron.

93
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:52,440
But there's no one new around here.

94
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,566
Father, there is one.

95
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,402
He actually just got back.

96
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:57,946
I saw him the other day.

97
00:03:58,613 --> 00:03:59,614
[indistinct mumurs]

98
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:03,451
[Munggo] Sir Delfin,
where's that son of yours?

99
00:04:03,534 --> 00:04:04,953
Why isn't he here?

100
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:06,496
- [crowd] Ah.
- [man] Where's Atoy?

101
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,164
He's still sleeping.

102
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:10,708
But I'll talk to him myself.

103
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,835
Not so fast, Sir Delfin.
He should face us as well.

104
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:13,795
- Right?
- [crowd] Yes.

105
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:15,922
- [crowd] Right?
- He owes us an explanation!

106
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:19,884
- Come on, let's go!
- [clamoring]

107
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,594
- Please, calm down.
- [clamoring]

108
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,473
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

109
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:28,434
[suave music playing]

110
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:30,144
[swishing]

111
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:34,732
[sewing machine whirring]

112
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,527
[swishing]

113
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:39,487
[snipping]

114
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:44,117
[sewing machine whirring]

115
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:47,078
[sewing machine whirring]

116
00:04:47,161 --> 00:04:48,121
[gun cocks]

117
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,249
[gun firing]

118
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:54,085
[clicking]

119
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,462
[snips]

120
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:05,513
[sewing machine whirring]

121
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:10,560
- Atoy! Atoy!
- Hey, Atoy!

122
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:12,270
- Hey, calm down.
- Face us! Get out of there!

123
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:13,896
[clamoring]

124
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:14,814
Atoy!

125
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:16,024
[crowd] Face us!

126
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:17,400
[crowd] Get out of there!

127
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:19,736
Bring him out! Bring him out!

128
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,362
- Bring him out! Bring him out!
- [chanting]

129
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,613
- Hey!
- Bring him out! Bring him out!

130
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:24,699
Hey, Emerson, enough
with this nonsense already!

131
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:28,494
Return the zippers and buttons you stole

132
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,746
before you dare show your face here!

133
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,873
Sir Delfin, this is no time
to play favorites.

134
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:33,374
You shouldn't even be here!

135
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:34,584
You're biased!

136
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:37,378
- Biased! Biased! Biased!
- [chanting]

137
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:39,964
- Biased! Biased! Biased!
- Bring him back! Bring him back!

138
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,507
Bring him back!

139
00:05:41,591 --> 00:05:44,677
Everyone, let's not act like this.
Please, calm down.

140
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:45,720
No! Give him back!

141
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:47,013
- Return Saint Anthony!
- That's right!

142
00:05:47,096 --> 00:05:49,307
Bring him back! Bring him back!
Bring him back!

143
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,933
- Return Saint Anthony!
- Hey!

144
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:52,852
- [exclaims]
- [splashes]

145
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:54,729
You people are making too much noise.
What do you want for me?

146
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:59,233
Atoy, you better return
the missing statue of Saint Anthony!

147
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,568
You're the only person
who could've taken it!

148
00:06:00,651 --> 00:06:01,611
Exactly!

149
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:02,653
- Yes! That's right!
- Exactly!

150
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,740
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

151
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:07,366
You people are completely
out of your mind!

152
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,326
Why would I do that?

153
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,786
Hey, Atoy,

154
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:12,246
you were the last person
in the church before it closed, right?

155
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,581
Remember?

156
00:06:13,664 --> 00:06:15,166
Also, you're the only outsider here.

157
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,294
So what? The dogs could be outsiders too.
Did you talk to them as well?

158
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:20,254
But the thing is,
you're actually a traitor.

159
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:24,092
You snitched to your dad, even after
I told you how important my job is.

160
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:27,220
You gave me your word,
and yet you still turned on me.

161
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:29,222
- Traitor!
- Traitor!

162
00:06:29,305 --> 00:06:30,389
- Traitor! Traitor!
- [Atoy] Ah.

163
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:31,557
[Atoy] It all makes sense now.

164
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,768
You're blaming me
because you want to get even.

165
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,394
Is that it, huh?

166
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:37,563
Just admit that you couldn't care less

167
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,816
about what really matters
in this barangay.

168
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:42,652
There's no doubt
that you stole the statue.

169
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,153
Exactly! That's right!

170
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:45,363
That statue matters so much to us!

171
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:47,031
It matters! It matters! It matters!

172
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:50,827
Whatever, keep pushing it until
my mother rises from her grave.

173
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:51,994
And I'll see to it you go with her.

174
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:56,582
You know, if there's anyone who truly
cares about Saint Anthony, it's me.

175
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,167
My mother was the one
who donated him to the church.

176
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,127
Right, Father?

177
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,837
Atoy does have a point.

178
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,881
Father, that was ages ago.

179
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:07,635
And Atoy, you've been gone
from here for so long.

180
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:09,804
How are we supposed to know if you've
been sneaking into people's homes?

181
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:12,682
Exactly, and I even saw you walking
around the streets last night.

182
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:14,475
- [Delfin] Calm down! Calm down!
- [overlapping chatter]

183
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:17,103
I'll talk to Atoy.

184
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,480
Just get inside, okay?

185
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:22,400
You're doomed, doomed. Doomed!

186
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:24,318
Doomed!

187
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,028
Doomed!

188
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:27,488
Doomed!

189
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,323
Doomed, doomed!

190
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:31,159
Doomed!

191
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:32,869
Doomed!

192
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,078
Doomed!

193
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,830
[people chanting in distance]

194
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:36,831
Stay here for now.

195
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,793
I'll call a barangay officer
to make them leave.

196
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:44,422
[people chanting] Doomed, doomed, doomed.

197
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:46,507
Did you really take
the Saint Anthony statue?

198
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:48,593
[tuts]

199
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:49,719
Wow.

200
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:51,137
Unbelievable that you actually
believe them.

201
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:54,932
Father, around what time
did you last see him at the church?

202
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,601
Around five.

203
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,269
Five o'clock.

204
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:01,105
But you got home at exactly nine o'clock.

205
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,356
[suspicious music playing]

206
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,900
Where were you for four hours straight?

207
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:05,776
Nowhere. I was just walking around.

208
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,321
And there's nothing wrong
with that. Right?

209
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:10,323
You walked around for four hours straight?

210
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:12,116
Who in their right mind
would do such a thing?

211
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,409
- Me!
- Why?!

212
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:16,537
I wanted to tire myself out.

213
00:08:16,621 --> 00:08:19,790
So that when I get home,
I wouldn’t have to see you or talk to you.

214
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,542
Wait, wait.

215
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:22,502
Don’t start fighting.

216
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:25,296
Father, I just don't get why
they would blame me for this.

217
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:26,631
Where are your things?

218
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:30,551
[suspicious music playing]

219
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,011
We need to get inside now.

220
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:33,971
For all we know,
those two could be up to no good.

221
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,473
Exactly! Sir Paldo has a point!

222
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:38,684
I'm sure they're trying
to bury the statue as we speak.

223
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,144
- Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
- Let's go.

224
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,355
Show a little bit of decency!

225
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,482
They're with Father Peping!

226
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:47,485
But Father Peping is on their side.

227
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:49,570
All the more reason we need to get inside.

228
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:51,948
- Right.
- Hey, stop!

229
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,574
Don't push through
with what you're planning.

230
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,117
This is straight-up trespassing.

231
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,619
Those two are just having a conversation.

232
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:58,955
I bet they're currently looking
for a way out of this.

233
00:08:59,038 --> 00:08:59,997
Exactly. That's right.

234
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,709
Emerson, you’ve worked
with Delfin long enough

235
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,836
to know he doesn’t allow
any wrongdoings to slip,

236
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,463
especially when it comes to his son.

237
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,257
So why are they taking so long in there?

238
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:11,175
- What exactly are they doing?
- Enough already!

239
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:15,721
[Atoy] You won’t find any statue in there.

240
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,392
[suspicious music continues]

241
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:20,518
[bag shuffles]

242
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:24,355
[Atoy] A statue
wouldn't even fit in there.

243
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,357
See? Nothing.

244
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:29,068
[suspicious music continues]

245
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,118
[thuds]

246
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,666
[Atoy] You're wasting your time.

247
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,377
[suspicious music playing]

248
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,176
You won't like
what you're about to see in there.

249
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,553
Did you hide it here?

250
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:58,889
Father, please come upstairs!
I've finally found it!

251
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,602
[suspicious music continues]

252
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,233
[tense music playing]

253
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,777
Mother of God. Is this all yours?

254
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,865
That's my collection.

255
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:19,327
Sorry to disappoint.

256
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,370
I told you you wouldn’t find
a statue in here.

257
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:22,455
But this is even worse!

258
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:26,626
Are you a murderer?

259
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,461
I didn't raise you to be this way.

260
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,297
Why do you always see the worst in me?

261
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,341
I'm just asking you a question!

262
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,384
You've been gone for a long time.

263
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:38,721
I barely recognize you anymore.

264
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:41,015
You've really changed.

265
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:45,019
And it's all because you chose
to rebel against me!

266
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,021
It's not what you think.

267
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:51,192
People have reasons.
There's always a reason why they change.

268
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:52,943
I haven't changed!

269
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,236
You!

270
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:59,492
I just can't believe you were able
to endure not seeing me for so long!

271
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:02,953
You're unbelievable! You held
onto that grudge for ten long years!

272
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:06,415
How is that my fault?

273
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:07,792
It is your fault!

274
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:10,461
It's your fault I went away
in the first place!

275
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:15,925
Think carefully about
why I left to begin with.

276
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:17,343
You have no one to blame but yourself.

277
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:19,470
[glum music playing]

278
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:23,224
[Barker] Baclaran! Baclaran!

279
00:11:23,307 --> 00:11:26,435
To everyone heading to Baclaran,
get in! Baclaran! Baclaran!

280
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:34,527
We're about to leave.

281
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,822
Yes, Mom.

282
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:39,407
I'm on my way home.

283
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:42,827
- [Delfin] How much?
- [taxi driver] 150, sir.

284
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,203
Here you go.

285
00:11:45,329 --> 00:11:47,373
- Keep the change.
- [taxi driver] Thank you, sir.

286
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,668
[Atoy] My group mate's house is a bit far.

287
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:56,757
[Barker] Baclaran! Baclaran!

288
00:11:56,841 --> 00:11:59,009
Mom, will you be going home with Dad too?

289
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:02,221
[Julie on phone] <i>No, he'll be home later.</i>

290
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:04,807
<i>He said he still</i>
<i>has to meet a client outside.</i>

291
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:07,351
Is that so? I see.

292
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:10,855
[exhales]

293
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:15,651
I'll go ahead now, Mom. See you later.

294
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:17,236
[somber music playing]

295
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:26,370
[somber music continues]

296
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:35,421
[somber music continues]

297
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,845
You've failed greatly as a father.

298
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:49,310
But your failure as a husband
is even worse.

299
00:12:49,393 --> 00:12:54,356
[brooding music playing]

300
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:00,779
Is there anything else you'd like to say?

301
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,406
Oh, Father is here. Perfect timing.

302
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,116
It's about time you made a confession.

303
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,409
[somber music playing]

304
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:08,245
Atoy, please, calm down.

305
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:11,582
No matter what his shortcomings are,

306
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:13,876
he is still your father.

307
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:16,212
Unbelievable, Father.

308
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,547
You keep saying that,

309
00:13:19,673 --> 00:13:23,677
and it becomes an excuse
for parents and older people

310
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:29,934
to get away with their wrongdoings
and betray their own families.

311
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,354
[somber music continues]

312
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:42,071
Why are you still here?

313
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:44,448
People are waiting outside.

314
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,117
Oh, all right.

315
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:48,369
I’ll face them myself.

316
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:52,456
[somber music continues]

317
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:05,928
[somber music continues]

318
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,481
Do you really think Atoy
could do such a thing?

319
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:20,568
He doesn't look like a thief at all.

320
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:23,529
- He's way too attractive to be one.
- [women] I agree.

321
00:14:23,612 --> 00:14:25,364
Just because he's handsome,
that doesn't mean he's innocent.

322
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:26,407
Right.

323
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:27,575
I bet you're his accomplice.

324
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:28,826
You're his accomplice!
You're his accomplice!

325
00:14:28,909 --> 00:14:30,160
You're his accomplice!

326
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:31,120
Hold it right there!

327
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:33,831
I'm far too good-looking
to be involved in any wrongdoing.

328
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,709
I can't say the same about you, though!

329
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:38,752
[clamoring]

330
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:41,088
You're hideous!
You're hideous! You're hideous!

331
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:42,965
Just let it slide!

332
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:45,467
- Let it go!
- [chanting]

333
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,678
Everyone, please, settle down.

334
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:51,307
I already went through Atoy's things.

335
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,100
Well…

336
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:54,184
What exactly did you find, Father?

337
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:55,352
- What did you find?
- I found nothing at all.

338
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:57,938
- None! None! None!
- [chanting]

339
00:14:58,022 --> 00:14:59,565
None! None!

340
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:01,150
- [indistinct chatter]
- [inquisitive music playing]

341
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,151
[Paldo] Nothing?

342
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:04,403
- [Paldo] As in, nothing?
- [crowd] Yes.

343
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:06,363
- [indistinct mumurs]
- [inquisitive music playing]

344
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:08,407
Wait a minute.

345
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,620
Did you guys even bother
going to the police? Did you?

346
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,538
[inquisitive music continues]

347
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:17,458
Or did you even bother
to talk to the church staff?

348
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:20,461
And whoever closed the church,
did you even speak to them?

349
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:22,713
[inquisitive music continues]

350
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:24,757
Ah.

351
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:28,260
So, you're just the type
to barge in and stir up trouble?

352
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:32,222
Atoy, don't you dare change the subject.

353
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:34,058
I'm sure you've already buried the statue.

354
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:35,100
That's why it's not in your house.

355
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:36,226
He buried it!

356
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:37,645
- He did!
- Really now?

357
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:38,812
Do you even have proof?

358
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:40,773
You are all good at that, accusing
someone of something they didn't do.

359
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,900
You came here without due process.

360
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:46,737
Don't be like those complete idiots
whose nails are bigger than their brains,

361
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:47,821
like Paldo.

362
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:50,824
[inquisitive music playing]

363
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:53,994
Atoy, we are really sorry.

364
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:57,164
Our emotions just got the better of us.
My apologies.

365
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:03,170
Everyone, let's go to the church
and talk this through properly.

366
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:04,964
Atoy, come with us too.

367
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:07,132
[inquisitive music continues]

368
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:13,764
[music fades]

369
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:19,144
[glum music playing]

370
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:24,108
Honey, please forgive me.

371
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:29,488
My past mistakes are catching up to me.

372
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:35,452
It seems like our son
already knows what I did to you.

373
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:42,126
[sobbing]

374
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:46,714
[glum music continues]

375
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,967
[sniffles then sighs]

376
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,301
[coughs]

377
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,386
[grunts]

378
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,806
Hold on.

379
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,934
Atoy, is your father not around?

380
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,729
[people murmuring]

381
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:04,773
[woman] Chairman's here.

382
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:05,899
[woman] He's here.

383
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,234
[man] We're just here
to give you an update.

384
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,611
I've already reported
the missing patron to the police,

385
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:13,115
but they consider it a low-priority case.

386
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:18,579
I also spoke with our staff,
and there was no-break in.

387
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:21,540
The main church door
was locked from the outside.

388
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:23,333
The lock wasn't tampered with.

389
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:27,963
Also, the door that the janitors used
to go out is located inside the office.

390
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:31,175
It was properly locked
and hadn't been forced open.

391
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:34,053
Maybe it just left on his own?

392
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:37,097
Miss Siony, what do you mean?

393
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:39,349
How is that even possible?

394
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,979
And it chose to disappear
because it didn’t want to be here.

395
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:47,483
Goodness, the world
really is full of sinners!

396
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:48,984
[indistinct murmurs]

397
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:51,153
And the number of churchgoers
has decreased.

398
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:54,198
Oh no, the patron must be upset, Father.

399
00:17:54,281 --> 00:17:55,324
How did you even come to that conclusion?

400
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:56,658
Are you close to the patron?

401
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:58,535
Well… just a thought. Hold on a second.

402
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:01,580
What if, somehow,

403
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:05,667
Saint Anthony just phased
through the wall and vanished?

404
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:07,753
That's why there was no break-in.

405
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:10,172
Would you like me to shove you
against a wall instead?

406
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:14,593
We're looking for a saint, not a ghost.
Only ghosts can slip through walls.

407
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:16,053
- True enough.
- [overlapping chatter]

408
00:18:16,136 --> 00:18:17,429
I see how it is.

409
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:20,057
Since you wanna be a know-it-all,
you take over.

410
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:22,518
I know more than you, that's for sure.

411
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:23,685
It's simple, really.

412
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:26,522
If there was no break-in from the outside,

413
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:27,564
that means…

414
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:31,485
the thief must have slept inside, right?

415
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:33,570
[indistinct chatter]

416
00:18:33,654 --> 00:18:34,530
[crowd] Yes, that works.

417
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:36,865
[brazen music playing]

418
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:39,368
[music fades]

419
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:51,380
[Cita] Delfin.

420
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:55,092
Delfin, everyone's at the church.

421
00:18:55,175 --> 00:18:58,470
I think Atoy will help track down
the culprit.

422
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,472
[pensive music playing]

423
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:05,269
Delfin, what's going on with you?

424
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:06,770
[sighs]

425
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,023
I think Atoy knows something.

426
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,609
What do you mean?

427
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:17,114
[somber music playing]

428
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:23,120
I think he's already aware
about what happened to us back then.

429
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:26,081
[Barker] Baclaran! Baclaran! Baclaran!

430
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:28,458
Baclaran! Baclaran!

431
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:31,003
- There's no more room.
- Baclaran! Baclaran!

432
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:34,173
Baclaran! Baclaran! Baclaran!

433
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:37,259
[Delfin] He simply chose to keep quiet.

434
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:41,847
But I feel like I hurt my own child.

435
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:44,099
And I didn't even realize it.

436
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:45,517
My God, Delfin.

437
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:48,312
What are we going to do?

438
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,314
What's going to happen now?

439
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:52,566
Is he mad at me too?

440
00:19:52,649 --> 00:19:54,401
Since he left,

441
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,863
he's only been talking to you.

442
00:19:57,946 --> 00:20:00,115
Even now, you two are still on good terms.

443
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,992
Atoy is only mad at me.

444
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:03,869
There's nothing for you to worry about.

445
00:20:03,952 --> 00:20:06,330
But I can't stay calm anymore.

446
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:07,789
Take it easy.

447
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:08,916
Don't worry about it.

448
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:12,502
I just need to face him.

449
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:15,881
I just don't know how…

450
00:20:15,964 --> 00:20:17,341
And I definitely don't know when.

451
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:19,509
[grunts]

452
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:22,346
[Delfin] I honestly
don't know how or when.

453
00:20:24,848 --> 00:20:26,225
[Cita] My God.

454
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:29,645
Cita, I don't want to lose my son again.

455
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:32,397
[somber music playing]

456
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,904
Anyway, why are you asking me?

457
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,991
Well, I'm just checking if those
with brains the size of beans

458
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,285
have grown as big as tofu.

459
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:48,705
But it looks like your companions
haven't gotten any smarter at all.

460
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:51,291
But don't worry, you can still
make up for it on the next question.

461
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:52,334
Okay?

462
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:53,877
[mischievous music playing]

463
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:56,505
Atoy, is there anything else
you'd like to add?

464
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:59,633
Father, it's simple, really.
Let's all use our heads.

465
00:20:59,716 --> 00:21:00,676
It's really basic logic.

466
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:03,303
If the thief was already inside,

467
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,264
it only means that it was unnecessary
to break the locks outside.

468
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:06,265
Right?

469
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:09,101
- Right.
- Right.

470
00:21:09,184 --> 00:21:13,814
He was already inside, and he simply
waited for the church to close.

471
00:21:13,897 --> 00:21:15,649
- Exactly.
- [overlapping chatter]

472
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:17,985
Then, he took the patron.

473
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:19,319
- Yes.
- Right.

474
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:23,740
Then, he simply passed
using the office door,

475
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:25,450
leaving no hint of suspicion.

476
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:26,410
He already had access to the inner lock.

477
00:21:26,493 --> 00:21:28,704
[overlapping chatter]

478
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:32,582
And before leaving with the patron,
he secured the door effortlessly,

479
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,335
leaving no trace of a break-in.

480
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:37,170
[Atoy] Awesome. That's it.

481
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:38,463
You're doing a great job.

482
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:40,048
I'll leave you guys to it. Good luck.

483
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:42,884
But Atoy, we still don't know who did it.

484
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:44,177
Could you please help us out?

485
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:47,014
- Please, Atoy.
- [overlapping chatter]

486
00:21:47,097 --> 00:21:50,892
So now you're asking me for help
after cornering me and blaming me?

487
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:51,893
Unbelievable.

488
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:54,021
I'm sorry, Atoy.

489
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:56,565
We shouldn't have listened to Paldo.
It really was his fault.

490
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:57,691
We're really sorry.

491
00:21:57,774 --> 00:21:59,151
I overreacted too.

492
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:00,986
I truly didn't mean it.

493
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:04,489
- I'm sorry, Atoy.
- [overlapping chatter]

494
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:05,907
- I'm terribly sorry.
- I'm sorry, Atoy.

495
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:08,493
You guys are lucky my mom
was the one who donated that saint.

496
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:13,498
So, at 1700 hours, the church was closed.

497
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:16,460
The full shutdown actually
happened about two hours later.

498
00:22:16,543 --> 00:22:19,338
So, who exactly closed the church at 1700?

499
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:21,465
[Siony] What's 1700?

500
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:23,508
Five p.m., uh, local time.

501
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:24,634
Just the two of us.

502
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:28,430
Actually, it was you,
Atoy, Rommel, and Boni.

503
00:22:29,139 --> 00:22:31,516
There was one high-probability target
near the perimeter.

504
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,351
- What?
- [Atoy] Right there.

505
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:35,312
[Atoy] I caught him kneeling here.

506
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:36,605
Sir, I'm really sorry.

507
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,106
We're about to close the church.

508
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:40,484
[Atoy] I think…
I think he was tying his shoelace.

509
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,194
[inquisitive music playing]

510
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:44,654
[vaccuum whirring]

511
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,616
[Atoy] Father and I were here,
on our way out,

512
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,034
but it was only him and I at the time.

513
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,243
<i>We didn't see anyone leaving with us.</i>

514
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:55,457
[Peping] <i>Atoy, be careful,</i>
<i>and send my regards to your father.</i>

515
00:22:57,292 --> 00:23:00,504
[Atoy] And if no one left with us,
it only means…

516
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:06,218
the thief could have gone here instead.

517
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:07,552
And at first, he will pick the booth.

518
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:08,970
He could've gone left as well.

519
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:12,015
[brazen music playing]

520
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:18,980
[claps] At the confession box.

521
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:21,024
[indistinct chatter]

522
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:23,944
[brazen music continues]

523
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:32,035
He hid in the confession box.

524
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:36,706
[Atoy] <i>He moved quickly and quietly,</i>
<i>so Ryan didn't notice him</i>

525
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:38,208
<i>while closing the door.</i>

526
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:40,252
<i>And Boni, who was sweeping here,</i>
<i>didn't see him either.</i>

527
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:41,545
<i>Zero noise.</i>

528
00:23:41,628 --> 00:23:43,296
<i>Zero visibility.</i>

529
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:44,339
<i>Precise entry.</i>

530
00:23:44,422 --> 00:23:48,635
[inquisitive music playing]

531
00:24:02,065 --> 00:24:03,483
What's that?

532
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:04,526
What's that?

533
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:07,154
What's this?

534
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:09,573
Urine.

535
00:24:09,656 --> 00:24:11,491
[chokes]

536
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,285
- That's the thief's urine.
- [coughing]

537
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:14,661
[mischievous music playing]

538
00:24:16,204 --> 00:24:17,998
- I think so too.
- But why would he pee there?

539
00:24:18,081 --> 00:24:20,208
After all,
there's a restroom in the office.

540
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:24,004
Father, how long did Boni
spend polishing the floor here?

541
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:26,298
About 40 minutes.

542
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:28,133
Instant relief.

543
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,594
[Atoy] <i>He couldn't hold it in anymore.</i>

544
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:33,638
So he had water with him, drank it all,

545
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:34,931
and peed right here.

546
00:24:35,015 --> 00:24:36,516
This means he brought water with him.

547
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,102
[Atoy] He was clearly planning
to stay here

548
00:24:39,186 --> 00:24:40,979
and steal Saint Anthony.

549
00:24:41,062 --> 00:24:45,984
If he brought water with him,
he probably had food with him too.

550
00:24:46,067 --> 00:24:48,111
- That makes sense.
- [Bunda] Right?

551
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:50,322
[Bunda, whispers] Right?

552
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,326
What?

553
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,369
I'm not going to sniff that.

554
00:24:56,453 --> 00:24:57,746
He did have food with him.

555
00:24:57,829 --> 00:25:00,290
He also brought bread with him?

556
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:03,960
How are we supposed to know
who the thief was?

557
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:05,754
I mean, almost everyone eats bread.

558
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:08,089
This doesn't seem
like ordinary bread. It's…

559
00:25:09,007 --> 00:25:10,050
It's dry.

560
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:11,551
Old bread.

561
00:25:12,636 --> 00:25:13,470
It has sugar on it.

562
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:16,264
Ah, sweetened old bread.

563
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:18,433
It's Biscocho.

564
00:25:18,516 --> 00:25:21,436
- Biscocho.
- [indistinct chatter]

565
00:25:21,519 --> 00:25:23,396
He was eating Biscocho.

566
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,981
This is Biscocho.

567
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:29,486
[funky music playing]

568
00:25:31,446 --> 00:25:32,822
[plastic rustles]

569
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:33,990
Mmm.

570
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:38,203
Does anyone know someone
who eats Biscocho?

571
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:40,872
Or anyone who's from Bacolod?

572
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:45,460
Atoy, I saw someone eating that yesterday.

573
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:47,754
They didn't even want to share.

574
00:25:47,837 --> 00:25:50,131
Dear, who did you see?

575
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:53,551
[brazen music playing]

576
00:25:56,346 --> 00:25:57,389
Oh?

577
00:25:58,265 --> 00:25:59,599
You better come clean, Paldo.

578
00:25:59,683 --> 00:26:01,893
Did you take the statue?

579
00:26:02,644 --> 00:26:04,813
Why are you blaming me?

580
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:07,023
I can't believe you're turning this on me.

581
00:26:07,107 --> 00:26:10,026
There were leftover pieces of Biscocho
in the church.

582
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:13,280
That's what the thief ate
while hiding inside.

583
00:26:13,363 --> 00:26:15,156
- Right?
- [clamoring]

584
00:26:16,199 --> 00:26:19,077
[Siony] Quit denying it!
Just drop the act already!

585
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,662
The kid was obviously telling the truth.

586
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:25,292
And didn't you mention that a girlfriend
from Bacolod was coming to visit you?

587
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:27,544
She probably brought Biscocho
for you as a gift.

588
00:26:27,627 --> 00:26:29,671
I have no idea what you're talking about!

589
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:30,964
You sure?

590
00:26:31,047 --> 00:26:33,341
- Really now?
- [snickers]

591
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:35,260
- Hey, that's enough.
- [clamoring]

592
00:26:35,343 --> 00:26:36,219
Let him be.

593
00:26:36,303 --> 00:26:37,470
Let him, so we can see for ourselves.

594
00:26:37,554 --> 00:26:39,139
[chairman] Give me a moment.
Let me take a look.

595
00:26:39,222 --> 00:26:41,391
- What's this?
- [plastic rustling]

596
00:26:41,474 --> 00:26:42,809
[overlapping chatter]

597
00:26:42,892 --> 00:26:44,060
[Siony] What's that?

598
00:26:44,144 --> 00:26:46,354
[crowd] That's obviously evidence.

599
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:47,522
[woman] Care to comment?

600
00:26:47,605 --> 00:26:50,692
You've been caught red-handed!
Guilty as charged!

601
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:53,361
- All right.
- Fine, I'll admit it. Okay?

602
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:54,696
This Biscocho is mine.

603
00:26:54,779 --> 00:26:56,823
And it was given to me
by my girlfriend from Bacolod.

604
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:59,951
But this doesn't mean
that I stole the statue.

605
00:27:00,535 --> 00:27:01,661
Okay?

606
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:03,621
I'm telling you,
someone's trying to set me up.

607
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:05,290
Oh, give me a break!

608
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:06,333
What an alibi!

609
00:27:06,416 --> 00:27:10,170
No one would waste their time
just to get you in trouble, Paldo!

610
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:13,048
Can you arrest that nephew
of mine already?

611
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:15,925
- Wait, please, just a moment.
- [clamoring]

612
00:27:16,009 --> 00:27:17,802
- I'm innocent.
- Hold on.

613
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:20,805
We can't just have Paldo arrested.

614
00:27:20,889 --> 00:27:24,225
Unless he confesses or we have solid proof

615
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:28,480
it was really him who took the statue,

616
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:31,191
we can't have him arrested or detained.

617
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:34,694
Everyone, the chairman has a point.

618
00:27:35,779 --> 00:27:38,740
But Paldo, for everyone's sake,

619
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:43,161
if you know anything about
the missing statue, just tell us already.

620
00:27:43,244 --> 00:27:45,330
[woman] That's right, Paldo.

621
00:27:45,413 --> 00:27:46,790
[overlapping chatter]

622
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:50,335
Father, why would I do such a thing?

623
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,545
I swear, I didn't steal it.

624
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:54,089
I swear on my life.

625
00:27:54,672 --> 00:27:55,757
It really wasn't me.

626
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,675
Please, believe me.

627
00:27:57,759 --> 00:27:59,677
[crowd] We find it hard to believe you.

628
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:00,887
[woman] You can be scheming.

629
00:28:00,970 --> 00:28:02,639
You can definitely be scheming!

630
00:28:02,722 --> 00:28:04,182
[Paldo] Father, it really wasn't me.

631
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:08,019
[Atoy] Father, don't count on Paldo.

632
00:28:08,103 --> 00:28:10,605
No criminal is going to admit
to a crime they did,

633
00:28:10,688 --> 00:28:12,065
even with proof staring them in the face.

634
00:28:12,774 --> 00:28:15,443
Then I guess all we can do
for now is pray.

635
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:18,905
Atoy, there's a prayer vigil
at the church.

636
00:28:18,988 --> 00:28:20,156
You should come.

637
00:28:25,495 --> 00:28:27,664
What we really need
to figure out is who he sold

638
00:28:27,747 --> 00:28:30,375
or pawned the statue to
and where it ended up.

639
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:33,169
I'm sorry, but I don't put much faith
in prayer vigils.

640
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:34,712
They won't change anything.

641
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:40,260
As the Bible says
in Mark chapter 9, verse 23,

642
00:28:40,927 --> 00:28:44,347
"All things are possible
for one who believes."

643
00:28:44,889 --> 00:28:46,057
You should go now.

644
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:49,102
[glum music playing]

645
00:28:54,357 --> 00:28:55,400
Hello?

646
00:28:56,484 --> 00:28:57,527
Hi.

647
00:28:58,111 --> 00:28:59,571
- [chuckles softly]
- Ah, Atoy.

648
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:04,492
I didn't see you at the church earlier.

649
00:29:05,076 --> 00:29:09,706
Well, I was hidden in plain sight,
watching you.

650
00:29:09,789 --> 00:29:13,710
It makes me proud to see you
using your skills as a soldier

651
00:29:13,793 --> 00:29:14,919
to serve the patron.

652
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,173
I actually find it kind of funny.

653
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,467
Because it’s so ironic, right?

654
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:21,968
Just think about it,

655
00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:26,473
the saint we pray to, the one we turn to

656
00:29:26,556 --> 00:29:29,184
whenever something or someone
goes missing,

657
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:31,686
well, he’s the one
who’s missing now. [scoffs]

658
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:34,939
But here you are.

659
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:38,985
If you really think about it,
you were meant to do this.

660
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:43,114
Maybe once the statue is back,

661
00:29:43,198 --> 00:29:46,785
the missing pieces in your life
will come back too.

662
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:48,328
Like…

663
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:51,664
your broken relationship with your dad.

664
00:29:52,332 --> 00:29:55,168
That wouldn't have happened
if no one caused the right.

665
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:58,963
Atoy, your dad isn't perfect.

666
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:04,093
Like everyone else, he has
his weaknesses, but he loves you.

667
00:30:04,177 --> 00:30:06,679
- [sobs]
- [somber music playing]

668
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:08,056
[sniffles]

669
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:09,224
[sobs]

670
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:13,228
Did Dad convince you to talk to me?

671
00:30:13,311 --> 00:30:14,479
No.

672
00:30:15,438 --> 00:30:17,398
[sobs] No, not at all.

673
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:18,566
No, he didn't.

674
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:21,402
I’ve known for a long time
that you two aren’t getting along.

675
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:25,323
And I’m not going to ask why, but…

676
00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:29,035
but Atoy, I’m sorry.

677
00:30:29,118 --> 00:30:30,537
[sobbing]

678
00:30:30,620 --> 00:30:32,872
- Sorry. I'm really sorry.
- No, no, no.

679
00:30:32,956 --> 00:30:36,543
- Wait, why are you apologizing?
- Because…

680
00:30:36,626 --> 00:30:40,296
- Why are you saying sorry?
- Because there's nothing I can do to help.

681
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:41,673
[sobbing]

682
00:30:41,756 --> 00:30:45,218
- Sorry.
- Listen, you're not to blame here.

683
00:30:45,301 --> 00:30:46,261
You don't have to apologize at all.

684
00:30:46,344 --> 00:30:48,471
You did nothing wrong.
None of this is your fault.

685
00:30:48,555 --> 00:30:52,725
It’s just heartbreaking because your mom
was praying to Saint Anthony,

686
00:30:52,809 --> 00:30:54,394
hoping you two would make up.

687
00:30:54,477 --> 00:30:57,522
But then he disappeared,
and you two still never reconciled.

688
00:30:57,605 --> 00:31:01,150
[sobbing]

689
00:31:01,234 --> 00:31:03,236
I doubt that'll ever happen.

690
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:06,906
My relationship with my dad
is as lost as the saint who disappeared.

691
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:14,247
Perhaps Saint Anthony can work a miracle.

692
00:31:14,330 --> 00:31:18,543
And when he's found, maybe that’s when you

693
00:31:18,626 --> 00:31:20,420
and your dad can finally mend things.

694
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:21,588
[sobs]

695
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:24,674
[brooding music playing]

696
00:31:26,092 --> 00:31:27,343
Sorry.

697
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:28,511
No.

698
00:31:28,595 --> 00:31:31,139
[sobbing] Sorry, Atoy.

699
00:31:31,222 --> 00:31:33,474
You don't have to apologize.

700
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:35,018
I'm sorry if there's nothing I can do.

701
00:31:35,101 --> 00:31:37,520
[sobbing]

702
00:31:37,604 --> 00:31:39,856
- [electronic blipping]
- [stirring music playing]

703
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:53,202
Why is Miss Bebang dragging my sister
into that place full of sexy girls?

704
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:56,414
Introducing the fearless rookie…

705
00:31:56,497 --> 00:31:59,542
It's the Amazing Ame!

706
00:31:59,626 --> 00:32:00,752
UP NEXT

707
00:32:00,835 --> 00:32:02,712
Hey, Ame, you better fight back!

708
00:32:02,795 --> 00:32:06,007
- [grunting]
- [thudding]

709
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:06,966
[grunts]

710
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:07,884
Don't hold back.

711
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:09,010
Punch him.

712
00:32:09,093 --> 00:32:10,219
- [grunts]
- [groans]

713
00:32:10,303 --> 00:32:11,429
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

714
00:32:11,512 --> 00:32:15,266
I'm already trying to find out
who caused all this trouble.

715
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:16,976
It's the son of our tailor.

716
00:32:17,894 --> 00:32:19,103
His name is Atoy.

717
00:32:19,187 --> 00:32:20,229
Where can I find this Atoy?

718
00:32:20,313 --> 00:32:22,065
There he is. That's him.

719
00:32:22,148 --> 00:32:24,734
- [car revving]
- [thuds]

720
00:32:24,817 --> 00:32:27,654
Give me every detail you've got.
I'm going after that idiot.

721
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:29,364
Don't worry, I'll handle it.

722
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,157
Are you going back to work now?

723
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,117
[brazen music playing]

724
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:39,832
[swishes]

725
00:32:42,585 --> 00:32:45,880
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
